==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quinone
<hw>Qui"none</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Quin</ets>ine +
ket<ets>one</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A crystalline
substance, <chform>C6H4O2</chform> (called also
<altname>benzoketone</altname>), first obtained by the oxidation of
quinic acid and regarded as a double ketone; also, by extension, any one
of the series of which quinone proper is the type.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>chinone</asp>, <asp>kinone</asp>.]</altsp> <-- and
benzoquinone. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quinovic</ent>⟦br⟧
